President Muhammadu Buhari, on Monday, attended the All Progressives Congress (APC) campaign rally in Yola, Adamawa state. Bola Tinubu, the presidential candidate of the party; Kashim Shettima; vice-presidential candidate; Aisha Binani, APC governorship candidate in Adamawa; and Rotimi Amaechi, former minister of transportation, were at the rally. APC governors who attended the rally included Nasir el-Rufai of Kaduna, Atiku Bagudu of Kebbi, Mohammed Badaru of Jigawa, while Murtala Nyako, former governor of Adamawa, was also present. Below are pictures from the event.                